North America: The "AI-Ethics & Privacy" Deep Dive
Scenario: A US-based genomic testing company (like 23andMe) wants to use AI to predict future health risks for insurance companies.
The Innovation: You are auditing the Ethics of Predetermined Risk.

Title: The Genomic Privacy Frontier: Auditing AI Predictive Modeling under HIPAA & CCPA

Specialist: Melissa Rachel Wozney

The Issue: The company’s AI model may inadvertently create "Digital Redlining" by identifying genetic predispositions that could lead to insurance discrimination.

Technical Audit: Investigating "Model Poisoning" and "Data Leakage" where private genetic markers could be extracted from the AI’s public API.

Psychology & Ethics: Using the Psychology of Privacy, I developed an "Ethics Impact Assessment" to ensure AI predictions don't violate the Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act (GINA).
